  <section id="ethics">
    <h2>Ethical Use of AI for Resumes</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      The strongest way to use AI is as a coaching tool, not a replacement for your judgment.
    </p>
    <div class="prose-flow">
      <p>
        Ethical resume writing means your final document should still reflect your real abilities, accomplishments, and growth. AI can help rephrase content, improve tone, and surface missing details, but it should not invent experience or inflate your qualifications. Recruiters are not only looking for polished wording; they are looking for trust and credibility.
      </p>
      <p>
        A good rule is simple: if you cannot explain or defend a statement in an interview, it should not be on your resume. Use AI to improve clarity and structure, then review every line to make sure it sounds natural and truthful. That balance gives you the benefits of technology while protecting your integrity as an applicant.
      </p>
      <p>
        Responsible AI use also includes protecting your data and being thoughtful about automation. Before sharing resume content with any tool, check where your information goes and whether it is stored. The goal is to use AI intentionally: draft faster, edit smarter, and still keep the final decisions human.
